sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS users_with_more_than_100_tweets
FROM users
WHERE total_tweets > 100;

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed like flowers in gardens" refers to tweets with high engagement scores;
- "top-tier of engagement" translates to the top 10 tweets by engagement score within each topic;
- "most cherished seeds (hashtags)" means the top 5 most used hashtags;
- "fertile grounds (topics)" indicates the top 3 most discussed topics.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM tweets
WHERE favorite_count > 5;

SELECT tweets.tweet_id, tweets.text, users.name 
FROM tweets 
INNER JOIN users ON tweets.user_id = users.user_id;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM tweet_hashtags
WHERE hashtag_id = (SELECT hashtag_id FROM hashtags WHERE hashtag_text = '#specific_hashtag');

external_knowledge:
- "Less prolific tweeters": Users who posted fewer tweets compared to others; 
- "Active in 2022": Users whose tweet activity is focused on the year 2022;
- "Excluding the top 20% by tweet volume": Filtering out users who posted the most tweets, focusing on the bottom 80%.
